"title": "Isle of Lewis (Replica) Chess Set, Customisable Colours (Pieces only/Board not included)) Governor Walking Dead, Harry Potter",
"description": "Originally molded from the pieces themselves this is the replica version of the Lewis set.\r\nArguably one of the most famous of the recovered chess sets. The originals were discovered buried on the Isle of Lewis by a farmer in 1831 although the exact nature of their discovery is as shrouded in tales and theories as their reason for being there. Carved for the most part from walrus tusk the set is thought to have been made in the 12th century and shows not only a level of skill and artistry but a unique understanding of character. Most likely of Norwegian origin the 78 pieces 67 of which are in the British museum and 11 of which are in the Museum of Scotland give us several incomplete sets with different queens, kings, rooks etc these are representations of some of those pieces. \r\nWhen first discovered some of the pieces were described as being a deep red which is why i have done the set here in the traditional colors of mahogany and stained sandstone.\r\n\r\nCAMEOS:\r\nIsle of Lewis is the exact set* Ron and Harry can be seen playing with in the Great Hall in HARRY POTTER AND THE SORCERERS STONE (in the traditional colour palette seen here) although sadly i do not currently posses the ability to elevate it to wizards chess :)\r\nIt can also be seen in season 4 of THE WALKING DEAD in Black and Aged White (i can also add an eye-patch to the white king for the &quot;Governor&quot; piece) \r\nChoose Harry Potter for Sandstone/Mahogany or Walking Dead for Black/White from the colour selection \r\n*being the replica version there are some slight differences to the one seen (to knowledgeable eye)\r\nfor the Exact set seen in both Harry Potter and Walking dead see my other Isle of Lewis Listing.\r\n\r\nYou can choose any of the three pawn styles to go with your set\r\n\r\nPICTURED 4TH PHOTO: \r\nBack Left to right: Antique Gold, Mahogany, Sandstone Stain, Copper. German silver\r\nFront: Sandalwood, Silver\r\nFINAL PHOTO : Pawn 1 pawn 2 Pawn 3\r\n\r\nThe set is Made to order and takes at least 2 weeks from casting to completion.\r\nThis listing includes the pieces only the boards are just too heavy to feasibly send.\r\nEach piece is Cold-Cast by hand using Tufstone a polymer modified gypsum cement, then painted, glazed and felt bottoms attached.\r\nThis set requires a board with at least a 2&quot; squares,\r\nThe King is 3 5/8&quot; inches tall the Pawns are 1.1 5/8&quot; 2. 2 &quot; 3. 2&quot;\r\n\r\nChoose your favorite colour from the selection and then just let me know what you would like as your opposing colour. If you don&#39;t see a colour you crave there feel free to ask i might be able to do it.\r\n\r\nWe make each piece as strong as possible handled correctly they will last a lifetime but will break if dropped on a concrete floor for instance.\r\nWe ship in flat rate boxes as the sets are very heavy and do our utmost to wrap each piece as securely as possible.\r\n\r\nWe are happy to ship internationally but the even the flat rate tends to be pretty expensive. Feel free to inquire and i can see how much shipping would be to your country or if i know a seller closer to you.\r\n\r\nThank you for looking, feel free to email with any questions. :)",
